decisions: [
  "Moved study action dispatchers out of the provider value memo and wrapped them in useCallback([dispatch]) so LessonDetailPage effect deps stay stable across state changes.",
  "Made MARK_LESSON_OPENED idempotent within the same local calendar day to stop timestamp churn from retriggering the lesson-open flow.",
  "Scoped LessonDetailPage's mount effect to lessonId changes while continuing to register the IntersectionObserver against the active lesson sections.",
  "Removed install-time skipWaiting() so the service worker only activates immediately after the existing SKIP_WAITING user action.",
  "Added a ref-backed 420ms review lock plus disabled review buttons to block double taps during the flip-back window.",
  "Added pathname-based scroll restoration and null-guarded card and lesson title lookups so missing IDs degrade safely instead of crashing."
]
evidence: [
  "npm test -> 7 passed, 19 passed (2026-03-22 18:36 EDT).",
  "Verified public/service-worker.js no longer calls skipWaiting() during install and still handles the SKIP_WAITING message path.",
  "Verified LessonDetailPage effect now keys off lessonId and stable study callbacks, so it no longer retriggers from provider state churn."
]
open_risks: [
  "Service worker activation and lesson-section completion were verified by code path and test coverage, but not manually exercised in a browser during this turn."
]
summary: The study provider now exposes stable lesson action callbacks, LessonDetailPage only re-runs its observer setup when the active lesson changes, the service worker waits for the explicit SKIP_WAITING action instead of force-reloading on install, the review controls ignore rapid repeat taps during the flip-back window, and route changes scroll back to the top; the automated test suite passed on the resulting code, with only browser-level manual verification of the service worker and section-observer flows still outstanding.
